# Lightmelon Windows Beta release
This page will guide you throw how install, configure and run the lightmelon beta release on windows host systems.


## Installation
Please just download prebuild bundle from **removed**. You can build it via nexe and download chrome for free.
This bundle includes the single exectable, chromium browser and a sample configuration.

After downloading, just extract the zip and you should receive folling folder structure.
```powerhell
Mode                LastWriteTime         Length Name
----                -------------         ------ ----
da---l        12/4/2020   1:53 PM                chrome-win
d----l        12/4/2020   1:51 PM                config
d----l        12/4/2020   1:53 PM                result
-a---l        12/4/2020   1:51 PM      103213116 lightmelon.exe
```

## Configuration
The app utilized the headful chromium instance to extract the lighthouse reports.
In case you need to access secured pages, please at first start the chromium browser and log into each needed page.

For this, please just change directory into `chrome-win` and start the `chrome.exe` binary.
Now navigate to each hidden webpage like `https://app.powerbi.com` and login. Please enable **remember me** features if available. Verify if the login data is stored by restarting the browser instance and reentering the page. 

After login to each needed page, we need to pass the prepared chromium user to your app. For this, please navigate to the special page `chrome://version` in your chromium browser. We need to copy paste **Profile Path** as highlighted below:

<img src="data:image/png;base64,">

Please copy this path and paste it into the `config/app.json` file. Please remove the "Default" form the path.
```json
{
  "output": [
    {
      "type": "file",
      "folder": "./result/"
    }
  ],
  "workerInterval": 1000,
  "browser": {
    "executable": "./chrome-win/chrome.exe",
    "profilePath": "C:\\Users\\user\\AppData\\Local\\Chromium\\User Data\\",
    "userProfile": "Default"
  }
}
```

After setting the profile Path, we are ready to define all the pages to test inside the `config/pages.json` file. It's an array including PageConfig objects.
```typescript
export interface PageConfig {
  name: string, // used to name the final reports
  url: string, // url to test
  interval: number, // interval in milliseconds
}
```

Just define all pages to test like shown in the example blow.
```json
[
  {
    "name": "google",
    "url": "https://google.com",
    "interval": 10000
  },
  {
    "name": "rehkaFish",
    "url": "fisch.rehka.dev",
    "interval": 20000
  }
]
```


## Execution
Afer setting the profile path and pages to test, we are ready to run the application.
For this, just execute the `ligthmelon.exe` file. **Please ensure that all chromium instances are closed before running the executable. Otherwise the application will not work proplery.**

It will read the configuration file and start testing the pages. Results get stored into `./result` directory. Please consider, that the application opens chromium instances for each test. 

So we suggest to run it on a dedicated test host.
